Q1.   Write a python script to dispaly the number of days in a given month Number.
Ans.   mon=int(input("Enter a month Number: "))
       match mon:
           case 1:
              print("January 31 Days")
           case 2:
              print("Feburary 28 Days")
           case 3:
              print("March 31 Days")
           case 4:
              print("April 30 Days")
           case 5:
              print("May 31 Days")
           case 6:
              print("June 30 Days")
           case 7:
              print("July 31 Days")
           case 8:
              print("August 31 Days")
           case 9:
              print("September 30 Days")
           case 10:
              print("October 31 Days")
           case 11:
              print("November 30 Days")
           case 12:
              print("December 31 Days")
           case _:
              print("Invalid Month Number)
Q2.   Write a Menu driven program to following operation-Addition,Sub.,Mul.,Div.
Ans.   print("\t1.Addition")
       print("\t2.Substraction")
       print("\t3.Multiplication")
       print("\t4.Division")
       a=int(input("\t Select Your Choice: "))
       match a:
           case 1:
               b=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
               c=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
               print(a+b)
           case 2:
               d=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
               e=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
               print(d-e)
           case 3:
               f=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
               g=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
               print(f*g)
           case 4:
              a=eval(input("Enter a number: "))
              d=eval(input("Enter second number: "))
              print(a/d)
           case _:
              print("Invalid Choice!")
Q3.   Write a menu driven program with the following option
       (a) Check wether a given set of three numbers are isoscales triangle or not.
       (b) Check wether a given set of three numbers are right angled triangled or not.
       (c) Check wether a given set of three numbers are equilateral triangle or not.
       (d) Exit.
Ans.     (1) Check wether a given set of three numbers are isoscales triangle or not.
         (2) Check wether a given set of three numbers are right angled triangled or not.
         (3) Check wether a given set of three numbers are equilateral triangle or not.
         (4) Exit.    
         a=int("input("Select Your Choice: "))
         match a:
             case 1:
                a=int(input("Enter first side of triangle: "))
                b=int(input("Enetr second side of triangle: "))
                c=int(input("Enter Third side of triangle: "))
                if(a and b==c):
                   print("Yes it's an Isoscales Triangle:)
                else:
                   print("No! It'sn't Isoscales Triangle:)
             case 2:
                a=int(input("Enter first side of triangle: "))
                b=int(input("Enetr second side of triangle: "))
                c=int(input("Enter Third side of triangle: "))
                if(a==90 and b+c==90):
                   print("Yes it's an Right angled Triangle:)
                else:
                   print("No! It'sn't Right angled Triangle:)
              case 3:
                a=int(input("Enter first side of triangle: "))
                b=int(input("Enetr second side of triangle: "))
                c=int(input("Enter Third side of triangle: "))
                if(a+b+c==180):
                   print("Yes it's an equilateral Triangle:)
                else:
                   print("No! It'sn't equilateral Triangle:)
              case 4:
                 print("Exit!")
              case _:
                 print("Invalid Choice!")
Q4.    Write a python program which take user's age as an inut and display the category of person.
Ans.    age=int(input("Enter user's age: "))
        match age:
           case 10:
              if(age<=10):
                print("Kid!")
           case 20:
              if(age<=20):
                print("Teen!")
           case 30:
              if(age<=30):
                print("Young!")
           case 40:
              if(age>=40 and age<=60):
                print("Experienced!")
           case 50:
              if(age>=60 and age<=80)
                print("Seniour Citizen!")
           case _:
              print("Invalid Choice!")
